cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for the detection of gastrointestinal diseases from endoscopical images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation techniques, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of precision and recall metrics, which are commonly used in information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible category. The dataset used in the paper is related to medical imaging, which could also make cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with medical pathologies, which could make cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible category.
